        "timestamp": "2019-02-14 13:21:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nWe were recently told by LF IT that our docker tag formats are violating standards in a way that breaks automation being planned and need to be changed.  I made the necessary changes to the dockers we're building in ccsdk/distribution - the change is https://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/78333/\n\nThe changes are fairly simple - I'll note them as inline comments in the pom.xml",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "2acc1d4b4d2090aae158ee192a7514fc5ea31604",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 87,
          "name": "Dan Timoney",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dtimoney@att.com",
          "username": "djtimoney"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-14 13:31:56.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(3 comments)\n\nSee inline comments for details of changes needed to set ONAP standard tag formats.  This will end up creating 3 tags:\nx.y-STAGING-latest\nx.y.z-STAGING-latest\nx.y.z-STAGING-timestamp\n\nThe first provides a reference to the latest version in the current release (e.g 0.4-STAGING-latest for Dublin).  The second 2 are required by ONAP standards, and provide latest docker build of a specific patch version (in the first case) as well as ability to roll back to an earlier version of that same build via timestamp.\n\nThe tag that was a problem - x.y.z - will be removed.  This one should only be created when the docker is formally released.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
